
                        Section 2 - Notes
                         CMD Instruction

1.  Initial Dockerfile, build image and run.

    $ cat Dockerfile
    # Dockerfile for CMD instruction
    FROM unbuntu
    CMD echo "How many words here" | wc -w

    $ docker build -t cmd . 
    $ docker run cmd
    4

2.  Next Dockerfile, build image and run.

    $ cat Dockerfile
    # Dockerfile for CMD instruction
    FROM unbuntu
    CMD ["/usr/bin/wc", "-l", "/etc/passwd"]

    $ docker build -t cmd . 
    $ docker run cmd
    19 /etc/passwd

3.  Last Dockerfile, build image and run.

    $ cat Dockerfile
    # Dockerfile for CMD instruction
    FROM unbuntu
    CMD ["/bin/bash"]

    $ docker build -t cmd . 
    $ docker run -it cmd
    root@b31635c75cd4:/# exit
